money. As a theologian, my even bigger one is time. In both these cases I find myself in constant fear of losing either one or the other. So, hopefully in the future with AI technology in the field of accounting, it’ll help in allowing me to make a more accurate computation of my financial status. It’s not only for bank financing, but for collecting personal expenses too. With time, even FamilyMart cash-register will do.

As for scheduling, with open source software designed specifically and only made to plan, we could have an eidetic memory of diagrams and scheduled tasks ah ah ah !- sfsfefs but it’ll add even more man-made-labeled OCD. However, ikea furniture could be a pretty good way of trying out meditation, while staying on-task of building, painting, cleaning.

To be honest, I’d prefer to see how much of my brain will get taxed if studying quick and smooth. The index file of WikiLib is good but I need a mental filter. Sometimes I just want to know what’s the most important stuff at the time, which I generally know when I know them in the context of a bigger picture.

I hope the best for the suppliers, nice idea. Overall, their market is money making. Useful metal buying, nice way to recycle plastic buckets that stink chemicals into my skin, bunch of toy that would help me forget the world rather than produce interesting mechanic.

I’d love the idea of harvesting plastic buckets that mold,
